#!/usr/local/bin/perl -Tw
use vars qw( $DBHOST $DBTYPE $DATABASE $DBUSER $DBPASS $DEBUG $CLASS $DB $HTML 
             $OPTIONS $TITLE @ACTIONS $HTMLHEAD $HTMLFOOT $HTMLBODY $VERSION 
	     $ROOTCLASS $STYLESHEET );
$VERSION = "1.5"; 	

=head1 NAME

mysql_admin.cgi - Administer TCB::mysql database

=head1 SYNOPSIS

Unfortunately, no URL is available for public use.  You can see the man
pages for DBIx::Frame::CGI for some details, otherwise you probably just
want to try it out.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

mysql_admin.cgi is a customized version of DBIx::Frame's dbixframe.cgi
script, set up for internal administrative use by the TCB Group to work
with TCB::mysql.  Entries for all tables can be added, deleted, or
modified with this package.  

=head1 REQUIREMENTS

B<TCB::mysql>

